namedLocations.description: A ZIP Code is a postal code used by the United States Postal Service (USPS) in a system it introduced in 1963. The term ZIP is an acronym for Zone Improvement Plan; it was chosen to suggest that the mail travels more efficiently and quickly (zipping along) when senders use the code in the postal address. The basic format consists of five digits. An extended ZIP+4 code was introduced in 1983 which includes the five digits of the ZIP Code, followed by a hyphen and four additional digits that reference a more specific location.

transcript.text: In this video we will see how customer can see shipping price.
Before approving any quote, let's see an admin.
When a quotation is placed, admin has two options.
Second, depending on weight if admin is giving flat shipping price.
In such case customers are aware about shipping price but if admin is giving weight based shipping in such case customer can see shipping price only after approving quote.
So we have enhanced our system and now customer can see shipping price before approving quote.
After clicking on review or update quotation button under my quotes they will see a pop up of estimated shipping price.
Once customer will select shipping country and zip code, all available shipping type will be visible with shipping price.
If you have any queries, please contact us at support@onprintshop.com.
